com.ibm.team.build.ant.task

Class UnitLogPublisherTask

  • java.lang.Object
    • Task
      • com.ibm.team.build.ant.task.AbstractTeamBuildTask
        • com.ibm.team.build.ant.task.AbstractPublisherTask
          • com.ibm.team.build.ant.task.AbstractFilePublisherTask
            • com.ibm.team.build.ant.task.UnitLogPublisherTask
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    IStaticReset
    Direct Known Subclasses:
    CppUnitLogPublisherTask, MSTestLogPublisherTask, NUnitLogPublisherTask

    public abstract class UnitLogPublisherTask
extends AbstractFilePublisherTask
    Ant task to update a build result from a log file that was produced by some testing framework. This task expects the filePath attribute to be set to the path to the log file, or the path to a directory containing one or more log files. The path can be relative to the base directory of the build file or it can be an absolute path.

Optional attributes are:

  • componentMap - Specifies a path to a file containing package-name-to-component mapping information. The package name must match the package for the JUnit test suite class.
  • mayFailPattern - A substring of a test suite class name. Any test suite class name containing the pattern is allowed to fail without causing the overall build to fail. The pattern is a simple string (not a regular expression). If not specified, any failing test suite will cause the overall build to fail.

See AbstractFilePublisherTask for additional required and optional attributes.

Example component map file contents: 

      <component_mapping>
           <component name="Build">
               <includePackage name="com.ibm.team.build.*"/>
           </component>
 
           <component name="Filesystem">
               <includePackage name="com.ibm.team.filesystem.*"/>
           </component>
      </component_mapping>
